.TH "scmi_handle_get" 9 "scmi_handle_get" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
scmi_handle_get \- Get the SCMI handle for a device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct scmi_handle *" scmi_handle_get
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
pointer to device for which we want SCMI handle
.SH "NOTE"
The function does not track individual clients of the framework
and is expected to be maintained by caller of SCMI protocol library.
scmi_handle_put must be balanced with successful scmi_handle_get
.SH "RETURN"
pointer to handle if successful, NULL on error
